This will add the scroll pane to the `CENTER` of the `BorderLayout`. This will allow the scroll pane to take all the available space in the frame. Then the scrollbars will appear for the part of the panel that can&#39;t be displayed within the bounds of the scroll pane.

When you add the scroll pane to the WEST, it will attempt to respect the preferred width of the scroll pane, which is greater than the width of your desktop and appears to be causing the issue.

